headline: Supermicro Eyes 'Make In India' Move For AI Servers
summary: Super Micro Computer (SMCI) shares jumped over 7% on Thursday as the company weighs a massive expansion into India, exploring local manufacturing to tap into the country's booming AI sector. With Nvidia and AMD already pouring billions into "AI Factories" across the region, Supermicro's move signals a major shift in the global AI supply chain.
